  "original_title": "Hirunika says Ranjan\u2019s release to attract certain political groups",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Hirunika says Ranjan\u2019s release to attract certain political groups",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The objective behind the expected release of former actor-turned parliamentarian Ranjan Ramanayake may be to attract certain political groups, former Samagi Jana Balawegaya MP (SJB) Hirunika Premachnadra said today.",
        "While speaking to journalists, Ms. Premachandra said that the release of Mr. Ramanayake was a tactic by the Acting President to attract a target political group. \u201cWe saw the acting President visiting the soldiers who were injured in clashes with the protesters. We never saw him visiting the injured soldiers in the past. The objective of this would have been to build up his image. Promising to release Mr, Ramanayake could also be an exercise to build his image,\u201d she said.",
        "Asked whether the release of Ranjan Ramanayake could be a political deal, the former MP said it is not clear as the latter is a person who dislikes deals. \u201cHowever I feel that Mr. Ramanayake will come out as an Aragalist\u2019 she said at the same time.",
        "\u201cWe keep mum if people accept Mr. Wickremesinghe as the President in the event he is elected, but will fight on if people do not endorse it. At the same time election of Mr. Wickremesinghe as the President could create a bloodbath if criticism against him escalates,\u201d she said.",
        "\u201cIt is better if Mr. Wickremesinghe takes up a post in the UN ,\u201d she suggested.",
        "Further Ms. Premachandra said she does not condone torching Mr. Wickremesinghe\u2019s private residence. \u201cThe attack gathered momentum after some journalists were attacked by the security forces near his residence,\u201d she said.\u00a0 (Yohan Perera)"
      ],
